
# 🌍 Cisco BGP Protocol Configuration Guide

This README outlines a basic setup for BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) used in inter-domain routing.

---

## 🛠️ Basic Router Setup

```bash
enable
configure terminal
hostname ROUTER_NAME
no ip domain-lookup
```

---

## 🌐 Interface IP Configuration

```bash
interface FastEthernet0/0
  ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
  no shutdown
exit
```

---

## 🔁 BGP Configuration

```bash
router bgp 65001
  neighbor 192.168.1.2 remote-as 65002
  network 10.0.0.0 mask 255.255.255.0
exit
```

---

## 🔍 Verification Commands

```bash
show ip bgp summary
show ip bgp
show running-config
```

---

## 💾 Save Configuration

```bash
copy running-config startup-config
```

---

## 🧠 Notes

- BGP is a path-vector protocol and used between ISPs and large enterprises.
- Use public AS numbers or private ranges (64512–65535 for testing).
- Requires manual peer configuration.

---
